cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on video classification, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for reducing computational time, which involves training a student network to process fewer frames, which is a machine learning (ML) technique. Therefore, cs.LG (machine learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper uses the YouTube-8M dataset, which is a large-scale multimedia dataset, suggesting that cs.MM (multimedia) is another possible sub-category. The paper also involves processing natural language descriptions of videos, which suggests that cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.CL (computational linguistics) are also possible sub-categories.
